<Layout title="Base Building" description="Which buildings actually gate your HQ level in Last War: Survival, the Tech Center bottleneck rule, and what to skip or stagger.">
  <h1>Base Building</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0]">HQ level doesn't gate itself — a short list of specific buildings does, and one of them (Tech Center) gates almost every level from HQ8 to HQ30. Last verified: July 2026.</p>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p><strong>The one-line version:</strong> keep Tech Center within 1 level of your HQ, always — it's the single hardest wall in the game. Beyond that, only level the one Tank/Air/Missile Center matching your main squad, stagger Barracks and Drill Ground instead of maxing both evenly, and check your in-game requirements tab for the secondary building each HQ level demands — it rotates and isn't fully pinned down here.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>The Headline Fact: Tech Center Gates Everything</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">Tech Center houses the research tree, and from roughly HQ8 through HQ30, almost every HQ upgrade requires <strong>Tech Center at HQ level − 1</strong> — verified across three sources (one snippet-only). Fall behind on Tech Center and every subsequent HQ level stalls, not just the next one. This is the one building you should never let lag.</p>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>You get access to a second Tech Center after clearing District 102, and a third at HQ30 — running them in parallel is how you keep the level-behind rule satisfied without a single queue bottleneck.</li>
    <li>If you're choosing between Tech Center and literally anything else in the queue, Tech Center wins.</li>
  </ul>

