  <h2>HQ 15–30 Gate Structure</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">The verified spine is simple: <strong>Tech Center = HQ level − 1</strong>, required at essentially every level from HQ8 to HQ30, confirmed across three sources (one snippet-only). Each level also demands one secondary building, and that requirement rotates. The rotation below comes from a single source — <strong>cross-check your in-game requirements tab before committing resources</strong>, since exact levels can shift by patch or server.</p>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <caption class="sr-only">HQ level gate requirements, verified Tech Center spine plus single-source secondary rotation</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr><th scope="col">HQ level</th><th scope="col">Tech Center required</th><th scope="col">Secondary requirement <span class="text-[#8a96b0]">[VERIFY]</span></th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th scope="row">15</th><td>14</td><td>Wall 14</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">16</th><td>15</td><td>Alliance Center 15</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">20</th><td>19</td><td>Barracks 19</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">22</th><td>21</td><td>Drill Ground 21</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">25</th><td>24</td><td>Tank Center 24</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">30</th><td>29</td><td>Drill Ground 29</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">The secondary slot rotates roughly Wall → Alliance Center → Tank Center → Hospital → Barracks → Drill Ground across the full HQ range — this is a pattern observation from a single source, not a confirmed formula. Treat it as "expect one of these," not a fixed schedule.</p>

  <h3>Practical priority order</h3>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Tech Center — never let it fall behind HQ level.</li>
    <li>Whatever secondary building your <em>next</em> HQ level demands (check the requirements tab).</li>
    <li>Your one Tank/Air/Missile Center — combat power, not a gate, but it's your main damage lever.</li>
    <li>Gear Factory to Lv20, then deprioritize.</li>
    <li>Barracks and Drill Ground, staggered rather than maxed evenly (see below).</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>What to Skip or Stagger</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Only level the Tank/Air/Missile Center matching your main squad type.</strong> If you're running Tank as your carry type, Air and Missile Centers can sit untouched — they don't gate anything for you and the boost only applies to their own type.</li>
    <li><strong>Stagger Barracks and Drill Ground ("waterfall training") instead of maxing both evenly</strong> — verified across two sources. Push one ahead to unlock the next troop tier, then bring the other up to match, rather than leveling them in lockstep.</li>
    <li>Resource-production buildings (Field, Mine, Vault-type structures) — keep these low relative to combat buildings. This is a medium-confidence, genre-wide pattern rather than a Last War-specific citation, so treat it as directional rather than precise.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contested: Material Workshop Priority</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">The community genuinely disagrees here, and this page won't launder it into settled advice:</p>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Skip-it camp:</strong> treats Material Workshop as a resource trap — Screws feed only the Gear Factory, and early Screw demand is low enough that building it out doesn't pay off relative to combat buildings.</li>
    <li><strong>Prioritize-it camp:</strong> a dedicated gear-progression guide argues Material Workshop should be built up early because Screw shortages become the actual bottleneck on gear leveling once you're mid-game, and by then you're behind on a queue that takes a long time to catch up.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-sm">Both camps come from usable sources; neither is a Tier-1 slam dunk. If your gear is already outpacing your Screw income, lean toward building more workshops (up to 5 are buildable). If gear isn't your bottleneck yet, the skip-it camp's logic holds. See the <a href="/upgrade-roadmap" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">Upgrade Roadmap</a> for how gear fits into your broader spend order.</p>

  <h2>Healing: Hospital and the Emergency Center</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Hospital capacity trends upward</strong> from roughly 650 at Lv1 toward 2,000–2,100 by Lv30–35 — confirmed on the trend by two sources, but they diverge on the intermediate values, so no level-by-level chart is published here. Troops beyond Hospital capacity when wounded are lost permanently, not queued.</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Center (the "ICU") is the real overflow mechanic</strong>, not a bigger Hospital. It unlocks at HQ22 and recovers a percentage of troops that would otherwise be lost once Hospital capacity is exceeded, converting them into recoverable "fainted units" instead. The Lv1 recovery figures circulating (~21% / 450 units) trace back to a single lineage of sources — treat them as approximate.</li>
    <li><strong>No public capacity formula exists</strong> tying Hospital level to safe troop counts, and no verified multi-hospital stagger pattern exists either. Don't trust a heuristic that claims otherwise — build Hospital and Emergency Center up together as your troop count grows, and don't overcommit to offense faster than your healing capacity can absorb losses.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-[#8a96b0]">Sources: lastwar.wiki (Tech Center, Gear Factory, Drill Ground, Hospital, Emergency Center, Wall, Alliance Center building pages), theriagames.com (HQ gate guide, Gear Factory HQ9 unlock corroboration, per-type Tank/Air/Missile Center guide, Emergency Center HQ22 unlock guide, Material Workshop priority guide, Wall guide, Alliance Center guide), cpt-hedge.com (Tech Center snippet, buildings index corroborating the single-type Tank/Air/Missile Center rule — snippet-verified only, not directly fetched, T11 troops/waterfall training guide, Material Workshop skip-it synthesis), lastwarvault.com (waterfall training guide), heaven-guardian.com (Hospital, Wall). Items marked [VERIFY] rely on a single source or on sources that likely share one origin — cross-check against your in-game requirements tab before planning around exact numbers. The Material Workshop section is presented as contested, not resolved.</p>
</Layout>
